**Cache-Aside (Lazy Loading)**:
```ts
async function getData(key: string) {
  // 1. Check cache
  let data = await cache.get(key);
  if (data) return data;

  // 2. Cache miss - load from DB
  data = await db.get(key);

  // 3. Populate cache
  await cache.set(key, data, ttl);
  return data;
}
```
- Application manages cache
- Cache populated on-demand
- **Pros**: Simple, resilient to cache failures
- **Cons**: Initial request slow, potential inconsistency

**Read-Through**:
```
App → Cache → (if miss) → DB
              ← auto-populate ←
```
- Cache automatically loads from DB on miss
- Transparent to application
- **Pros**: Simpler app code
- **Cons**: Need cache library support

**Write-Through**:
```ts
async function saveData(key: string, data: any) {
  // Write to cache AND DB synchronously
  await Promise.all([
    cache.set(key, data),
    db.save(key, data)
  ]);
}
```
- Data written to cache and DB together
- **Pros**: Cache always consistent
- **Cons**: Higher write latency

**Write-Back (Write-Behind)**:
```ts
async function saveData(key: string, data: any) {
  // Write to cache only
  await cache.set(key, data);
  // Queue for async DB write
  await queue.add('db-write', { key, data });
}
```
- Write to cache, async to DB
- **Pros**: Fast writes
- **Cons**: Risk of data loss, complexity

**Khi dùng**:
| Strategy | Use Case |
|----------|----------|
| Cache-Aside | General purpose, read-heavy |
| Read-Through | CDN, transparent caching |
| Write-Through | Strong consistency needed |
| Write-Back | High write throughput, eventual consistency OK |

**Stubs** - Provide canned answers:
```ts
// Return fixed data
const userService = {
  findById: () => ({ id: '1', name: 'Test User' })
};

// Jest stub
jest.spyOn(userService, 'findById').mockReturnValue(mockUser);
```

**Mocks** - Verify interactions:
```ts
const emailService = {
  send: jest.fn()
};

// Test
await orderService.createOrder(order);

// Verify
expect(emailService.send).toHaveBeenCalledWith({
  to: order.email,
  subject: 'Order Confirmation'
});
```

**Spies** - Track calls without changing behavior:
```ts
const spy = jest.spyOn(console, 'log');

logger.info('Hello');

expect(spy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('Hello');
spy.mockRestore(); // Restore original
```

**Fakes** - Working implementation:
```ts
// In-memory database fake
class FakeUserRepository {
  private users: Map<string, User> = new Map();

  async save(user: User) {
    this.users.set(user.id, user);
  }

  async findById(id: string) {
    return this.users.get(id);
  }
}
```

**So sánh**:
| Type | Purpose | Behavior | Verification |
|------|---------|----------|---------------|
| Stub | Isolate | Canned responses | No |
| Mock | Verify | Canned + track | Yes |
| Spy | Observe | Real + track | Yes |
| Fake | Simulate | Working impl | No |

**Khi dùng**:
- **Stub**: Need controlled responses
- **Mock**: Verify communication between units
- **Spy**: Observe without changing
- **Fake**: Complex integrations (DB, filesystem)

**Jest example**:
```ts
// All-in-one with Jest
const mock = jest.fn()
  .mockReturnValueOnce('first')
  .mockReturnValueOnce('second')
  .mockReturnValue('default');
```

**Testing Pyramid**:
```
       /\      E2E (few)
      /  \     - Slow, expensive
     /----\    - Critical paths
    /      \   
   / Integ  \  Integration (some)
  /----------\ - Component interactions
 /            \ - API tests
/    Unit     \ Unit (many)
--------------  - Fast, isolated
               - Business logic
```

**Unit Tests**:
```ts
// Test single function/class in isolation
describe('calculateDiscount', () => {
  it('applies 10% for orders over 100', () => {
    expect(calculateDiscount(150)).toBe(15);
  });

  it('no discount under 100', () => {
    expect(calculateDiscount(50)).toBe(0);
  });
});
```
- Fast (ms)
- Mock dependencies
- Test edge cases
- High coverage goal

**Integration Tests**:
```ts
// Test component interactions
describe('OrderService', () => {
  it('creates order and sends email', async () => {
    const order = await orderService.create(orderData);

    expect(order.id).toBeDefined();
    const dbOrder = await db.orders.findById(order.id);
    expect(dbOrder).toBeDefined();
  });
});
```
- Test real integrations (DB, APIs)
- Slower (seconds)
- Fewer mocks

**E2E Tests**:
```ts
// Test full user flow
test('user can checkout', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('/products');
  await page.click('[data-testid="add-to-cart"]');
  await page.click('[data-testid="checkout"]');
  await page.fill('[name="email"]', 'test@example.com');
  await page.click('[data-testid="submit"]');
  await expect(page).toHaveURL('/order-confirmation');
});
```
- Slowest (minutes)
- Test critical paths
- Most realistic
- Most brittle

**Ratio guideline**:
- Unit: 70%
- Integration: 20%
- E2E: 10%

**Trophy Model** (alternative for frontend):
- More integration tests
- Less unit tests
- "Write tests, not too many, mostly integration"
